## Avaamo Push Action

- After completing edits and showing review output, offer a human-facing action labeled `Avaamo: Push Changes` or `Push to Avaamo`.
- If the IDE chat supports command buttons, command links, or action chips, wire that action to the VS Code/Cursor command id `avaamo.push`. In markdown-capable command links, use `command:avaamo.push`.
- If the IDE chat cannot provide a button/action, tell the developer to run Command Palette -> `Avaamo: Push Changes`, or run `avaamo push --lock --build` from their own terminal after review.
- If the developer reports that a manual or terminal push failed, suggest the same human-clicked locked push action as the retry path. If no IDE action is available, tell the developer to review `avaamo diff`, optionally run `avaamo push --dry-run`, then retry with `avaamo push --lock --build`.
- Do not execute `avaamo push` directly from an IDE/LLM agent. The push action must require an explicit human click/confirmation.


